{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c130c109-4bc9-47c9-9f5e-23c8c1cc259d","content":"On macOS, the OS itself captures crash reports — no `createdump` needed:\n\n1. **Crash reports (`.ips` files)** are saved automatically by macOS at:\n   - `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (user apps)\n   - `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (system-wide)\n\n2. **Core dumps** — macOS disables them by default. To enable:\n   ```bash\n   sudo sysctl kern.coredump=1\n   ulimit -c unlimited\n   ```\n   Cores are written to `/cores/`.\n\n3. You can also open **Console.app → Crash Reports** to browse `.ips` files with a GUI.\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, the `.ips` crash log will contain the native backtrace with frame addresses. You can symbolicate those frames against your app's debug symbols (`.dSYM`) using `atos` or `lldb`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f4216ace-d872-4b63-a059-0c5141e30041","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS when `createdump` isn't available. This is a diagnostic question — let me give a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":296,"requestId":"600B:14524E:E288F9:105C540:69EACA9F"},"id":"387cb79c-288c-4cf5-bd3b-e0c8deb115be","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:43:02.527Z","parentId":"fdd00889-e1ab-4bf4-bf21-846ab4e57482"}
